1
00:48:24,300 --> 00:48:26,468
KILI:
Come on! Get up!

2
00:48:26,761 --> 00:48:28,052
- Bilbo!
- Don't!

3
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:31,681
Lay down your arms...

4
00:48:32,349 --> 00:48:34,142
...or we'll rip his off.

5
00:48:41,859 --> 00:48:43,318
[SWORD CLANGS]

6
00:48:48,783 --> 00:48:50,784
NORI:
Oh! That's hot, that's hot, that's hot!

7
00:48:50,951 --> 00:48:52,577
Don't bother cooking them.

8
00:48:52,745 --> 00:48:56,998
Let's just sit on them
and squash them into jelly.

9
00:48:57,166 --> 00:49:01,377
They should be sautéed and grilled
with a sprinkle of sage.

10
00:49:01,545 --> 00:49:03,087
BALIN:
Is this really necessary?

11
00:49:03,255 --> 00:49:05,048
That does sound quite nice.

12
00:49:05,216 --> 00:49:07,634
BOMBUR: Untie me, mister.
GLOIN: Eat someone your own size.

13
00:49:08,344 --> 00:49:10,261
WILLIAM:
Never mind the seasoning.

14
00:49:10,429 --> 00:49:12,222
We ain't got all night.

15
00:49:12,389 --> 00:49:15,725
Dawn ain't far away.
Let's get a move on.

16
00:49:15,893 --> 00:49:18,311
I don't fancy being turned to stone.

17
00:49:21,023 --> 00:49:22,357
BILBO:
Wait!

18
00:49:22,525 --> 00:49:25,568
You are making a terrible mistake.

19
00:49:25,736 --> 00:49:27,946
You can't reason with them. They're half-wits!

20
00:49:28,113 --> 00:49:30,198
Half-wits? What does that make us?

21
00:49:30,825 --> 00:49:33,618
I meant with the seasoning.

22
00:49:33,953 --> 00:49:36,579
What about the seasoning?

23
00:49:36,747 --> 00:49:37,997
Well, have you smelt them?

24
00:49:38,332 --> 00:49:41,876
You're gonna need something stronger
than sage before you plate this lot up.

25
00:49:42,044 --> 00:49:45,171
BOMBUR: Traitor!
- What do you know about cooking Dwarf?

26
00:49:45,714 --> 00:49:46,756
BERT:
Shut up.

27
00:49:47,091 --> 00:49:50,760
Let the flurgaburburahobbit talk.

28
00:49:51,679 --> 00:49:54,597
The secret to cooking Dwarf is....

29
00:49:54,765 --> 00:49:57,892
BERT: Yes? Come on. Tell us the secret.
- It's, uh....

30
00:49:58,060 --> 00:50:00,103
Yes, I'm telling you. The secret is...

31
00:50:02,648 --> 00:50:04,399
...to skin them first.

32
00:50:04,567 --> 00:50:06,484
NORI:
What? Skin us?

33
00:50:06,652 --> 00:50:09,195
Tom, get me filleting knife.

34
00:50:09,363 --> 00:50:11,030
I'll skin you, you little--!

35
00:50:11,198 --> 00:50:13,074
DWALIN:
I won't forget that. I won't forget it.

36
00:50:13,242 --> 00:50:15,577
What a load of rubbish.

37
00:50:15,744 --> 00:50:18,663
I've eaten plenty with their skins on.

38
00:50:18,831 --> 00:50:21,207
Scarf them, I say, boots and all.

39
00:50:21,834 --> 00:50:24,127
TOM:
He's right.

40
00:50:24,295 --> 00:50:26,921
Nothing wrong with a bit of raw Dwarf.

41
00:50:29,633 --> 00:50:31,843
Nice and crunchy.

42
00:50:32,177 --> 00:50:34,721
Oh, not that one. He's infected.

43
00:50:35,014 --> 00:50:36,639
- Huh?
- You what?

44
00:50:36,807 --> 00:50:40,935
Yeah, he's got worms in his... tubes.

45
00:50:41,103 --> 00:50:43,062
TOM: Eww!
BOMBUR: Aah!

46
00:50:43,314 --> 00:50:46,608
In fact, they all have.
They're infested with parasites.

47
00:50:46,775 --> 00:50:49,736
It's a terrible business.
I wouldn't risk it. I really wouldn't.

48
00:50:49,904 --> 00:50:51,779
Parasites? Did he say "parasites"?

49
00:50:51,947 --> 00:50:54,741
We don't have parasites. You have parasites!

50
00:50:55,492 --> 00:50:57,410
OIN:
What are you talking about, laddie?

51
00:50:57,578 --> 00:50:58,828
[KILI GRUNTS]

52
00:51:00,956 --> 00:51:02,832
I've got parasites as big as my arm.

53
00:51:03,000 --> 00:51:05,585
Mine are the biggest parasites.
I've got huge parasites.

54
00:51:05,753 --> 00:51:07,420
[DWARVES CHATTERING]

55
00:51:07,630 --> 00:51:09,088
KILI: We're riddled.
ORI: Yes, I'm riddled.

56
00:51:09,256 --> 00:51:10,548
Yes, we are, badly.

57
00:51:10,716 --> 00:51:13,593
What would you have us do, then?

58
00:51:13,761 --> 00:51:15,303
Let them all go?

59
00:51:15,679 --> 00:51:19,015
- Well....
- You think I don't know what you're up to?

60
00:51:19,433 --> 00:51:23,519
This little ferret is taking us for fools.

61
00:51:23,979 --> 00:51:25,521
- Ferret?
- Fools?

62
00:51:25,689 --> 00:51:28,650
GANDALF:
The dawn will take you all!

63
00:51:30,069 --> 00:51:31,694
- Who's that?
- No idea.

64
00:51:31,862 --> 00:51:32,987
Can we eat him too?

65
00:51:36,367 --> 00:51:38,076
[TROLLS GROANING]

66
00:51:51,882 --> 00:51:53,633
[ALL LAUGHING]

67
00:51:59,139 --> 00:52:01,683
Get your foot out of my back.

68
00:52:02,017 --> 00:52:04,268
[GRUNTING]

69
00:52:04,436 --> 00:52:06,437
[DWARVES CHATTERING]

70
00:52:07,501 --> 00:52:08,940
[IMITATES TROLL GROAN]

71
00:52:11,193 --> 00:52:13,361
Where did you go to, if I may ask?

72
00:52:13,529 --> 00:52:15,196
To look ahead.

73
00:52:15,572 --> 00:52:18,408
- What brought you back?
- Looking behind.

74
00:52:19,410 --> 00:52:20,618
Nasty business.

75
00:52:20,786 --> 00:52:22,286
Still, they're all in one piece.

76
00:52:22,454 --> 00:52:23,955
No thanks to your burglar.

77
00:52:25,416 --> 00:52:27,500
He had the nous to play for time.

78
00:52:28,919 --> 00:52:31,295
None of the rest of you thought of that.

